CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 30, 1941, pg. 3, reads: "Military Visitor - "Johnny came marching home again" last week when Johnny Woodruff, now Second Lieutenant with the 369th, stationed at Oswego, New York, came home for old time's sake. Johnny, who came here from Washington, D.C., reports fine treatment, good food, and praised his superior officers highly.  Johnny is in charge of the track teams and has weeded his squads from a total of over 100 to approximately fifty athletes.  His teams have won prizes in Pennsylvania, Delaware, New Jersey, and New York.  Woodruff is recovering from a recent major operation but is now able to resume his military duties. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: John "Johnny" Woodruff, Second Lieutenant of the 369th regiment, standing outdoors in front of brick building
